{{<h1 style="padding-bottom: 10px; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-top: 5px;"> / &nbsp; Mario Souto }}
~~~

~~~
{}{img_left}{./images/mario_souto_profile.jpeg}{alt text}{200}{200}{IMGLINKTARGET}

I'm an engineer specializing in AI, control, and optimization, with a focus on enhancing energy systems and battery storage. After earning my PhD in Electrical Engineering, I worked at AWS, where I developed AI models to optimize Amazon's renewable energy portfolio. I was the tech lead for the Renewable Energy Optimization (REO) team, and the technology I developed contributed to Amazon becoming one of the world's largest corporate buyers of renewable energy. Later, I was the tech lead at Equilibrium Energy, where I developed and deployed grid-scale battery control and optimization algorithms.

During my PhD, I created a novel algorithm and solver for Semidefinite Programming problems, a somewhat exotic subset of convex optimization problems. Since then, my research has revolved around model predictive control, optimization algorithms, and machine learning.
~~~

